    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A broad term applied to various printmaking processes used mainly by French engravers in the late 18th century, and which imitated the look of ink, gouache, or watercolor drawings. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
